  "prompt": "How do I capture raw images from an Android camera?",
  "response": "Capturing Raw Images from an Android Camera\n=============================================\n\nCapturing raw images from an Android camera requires using the Camera2 API, which provides more advanced features and control over the camera compared to the older Camera API. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to capture raw images from an Android camera.\n\n**Prerequisites**\n\n* Android API level 21 (Lollipop) or higher\n* Camera2 API support\n\n**Code**\n\nBelow is an example code snippet that demonstrates how to capture raw images from an Android camera using the Camera2 API.\n\n```java\n// Import necessary packages\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CameraAccessException;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CameraCaptureSession;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CameraCharacteristics;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CameraDevice;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CameraManager;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CaptureRequest;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.CaptureResult;\nimport android.hardware.camera2.TotalCaptureResult;\nimport android.media.Image;\nimport android.media.ImageReader;\nimport android.os.Bundle;\nimport android.util.Log;\nimport android.view.Surface;\n\nimport androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;\n\npublic class RawImageCaptureActivity extends AppCompatActivity {\n\n    private static final String TAG = \"RawImageCaptureActivity\";\n\n    private CameraDevice cameraDevice;\n    private CameraCaptureSession captureSession;\n    private ImageReader imageReader;\n\n    @Override\n    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_raw_image_capture);\n\n        // Get the camera manager\n        CameraManager cameraManager = (CameraManager) getSystemService(CAMERA_SERVICE);\n\n        try {\n            // Get the camera ID\n            String[] cameraIds = cameraManager.getCameraIdList();\n            String cameraId = cameraIds[0];\n\n            // Open the camera\n            cameraManager.openCamera(cameraId, new CameraDevice.StateCallback() {\n                @Override\n                public void onOpened(CameraDevice camera) {\n                    cameraDevice = camera;\n                    createCaptureSession();\n                }\n\n                @Override\n                public void onDisconnected(CameraDevice camera) {\n                    cameraDevice.close();\n                }\n\n                @Override\n                public void onError(CameraDevice camera, int error) {\n                    Log.e(TAG, \"Camera error: \" + error);\n                }\n            }, null);\n        } catch (CameraAccessException e) {\n            Log.e(TAG, \"Camera access exception: \" + e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void createCaptureSession() {\n        try {\n            // Create an ImageReader to receive the raw images\n            imageReader = ImageReader.newInstance(1920, 1080, ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR, 2);\n\n            // Create a capture request\n            CaptureRequest.Builder captureRequestBuilder = cameraDevice.createCaptureRequest(CameraDevice.TEMPLATE_PREVIEW);\n            captureRequestBuilder.addTarget(imageReader.getSurface());\n\n            // Create a capture session\n            cameraDevice.createCaptureSession(Arrays.asList(imageReader.getSurface()), new CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback() {\n                @Override\n                public void onConfigured(CameraCaptureSession session) {\n                    captureSession = session;\n                    captureRawImage();\n                }\n\n                @Override\n                public void onConfigureFailed(CameraCaptureSession session) {\n                    Log.e(TAG, \"Capture session configuration failed\");\n                }\n            }, null);\n        } catch (CameraAccessException e) {\n            Log.e(TAG, \"Camera access exception: \" + e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void captureRawImage() {\n        try {\n            // Create a capture request\n            CaptureRequest captureRequest = captureSession.getDevice().createCaptureRequest(CameraDevice.TEMPLATE_STILL_CAPTURE);\n            captureRequest.addTarget(imageReader.getSurface());\n\n            // Set the capture request to capture a raw image\n            captureRequest.set(CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE, CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE_ON);\n            captureRequest.set(CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AE_MODE, CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AE_MODE_OFF);\n            captureRequest.set(CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AWB_MODE, CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AWB_MODE_OFF);\n\n            // Capture the raw image\n            captureSession.capture(captureRequest, new CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback() {\n                @Override\n                public void onCaptureCompleted(CameraCaptureSession session, CaptureRequest request, TotalCaptureResult result) {\n                    Log.d(TAG, \"Raw image captured\");\n                }\n            }, null);\n        } catch (CameraAccessException e) {\n            Log.e(TAG, \"Camera access exception: \" + e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private ImageReader.OnImageAvailableListener onImageAvailableListener = new ImageReader.OnImageAvailableListener() {\n        @Override\n        public void onImageAvailable(ImageReader reader) {\n            Image image = reader.acquireLatestImage();\n            if (image != null) {\n                // Process the raw image data\n                ByteBuffer buffer = image.getPlanes()[0].getBuffer();\n                byte[] bytes = new byte[buffer.remaining()];\n                buffer.get(bytes);\n\n                // Save the raw image data to a file\n                // ...\n\n                image.close();\n            }\n        }\n    };\n}\n```\n\n**Explanation**\n\n1. The code first gets the camera manager and opens the camera.\n2. It then creates an `ImageReader` to receive the raw images and creates a capture request.\n3. The capture request is set to capture a raw image by setting the `STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE` to `ON`, `CONTROL_AE_MODE` to `OFF`, and `CONTROL_AWB_MODE` to `OFF`.\n4. The raw image is captured using the `capture` method of the `CameraCaptureSession`.\n5. The raw image data is processed in the `onImageAvailable` method of the `ImageReader.OnImageAvailableListener`.\n\n**Note**\n\n* This code snippet only captures a single raw image. To capture multiple raw images, you need to modify the code to continuously capture images.\n* The raw image data is stored in the `ByteBuffer` of the `Image` object. You need to process this data to save it to a file or use it for further processing.\n* The `Camera2` API is complex and requires a good understanding of camera concepts and Android development. This code snippet is just a basic example to get you started.",
